<L>__{interior ward night}
<A>__{frances turns to face the women in their cots. collects herself. looks repentant. she is practicing tomorrow's speech.}
<C>__{frances}
<D>__{i realize now that i was a very sick woman.}
<C>__{women in ward}
<D>__{sick! she's sick!}
<C>__{frances}
<D>__{i couldn't relate to others in a normal way.}
<C>__{one patient}
<P>__{(playful warning)}
<D>__{she's... not... normal...!}
<A>__{the others laugh. we realize that if frances can handle this, she can sail through it tomorrow. the catcalls gradually diminish as she concludes her speech.}
<C>__{frances}
<D>__{and i was not taking responsibility for my actions. but now, thanks to your treatment, i feel ready to face myself, ready to resume the career which i so single handedly shattered. i only hope... i hope i can make you all proud of me. thank you. thank you so much.}
<A>__{the room is silent now. a very odd moment. to their astonishment, the other patients seem to believe her...}
